fields.description:
I have successfully performed git svn clone using the feature in the latest SourceTree.

But, if I try to Pull (effectively, git svn rebase), then SourceTree complains about missing author map file.

It seems, SourceTree saves in .git/config a temporary location of the file specified at cloning stage (notice the mysterious /tmp/)

{code}
[svn]
	authorsfile = /tmp/d:/dev/geos/authors.svn
{code}

whereas correct setting is:


{code}
[svn]
	authorsfile = d:/dev/geos/authors.svn
{code}

I changed the .git/config file manually and SourceTree is happy to Pull the updates from SVN repository.
